cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the reduction of the size of deep neural networks through compression techniques. It also involves the efficient inferencing of compressed models, which falls under the domain of machine learning. Additionally, the paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with the inferencing of images. The use of parallel algorithms and memory constraints also suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the use of deep neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
